# Retrospective protocol

> ⚠️ **Stub — Phase 1.**

## When

After Reviewer signs off, before the Lead runs `Clean up the team`.

## Who

- Reviewer drafts findings
- Lead approves / defers / rejects
- Other teammates silent observers

## The mechanical pass

For each observed issue:

| Field | Example |
|---|---|
| What happened | "Feature engineer used write-then-reread for list mutations" |
| Auto-catchable? | "No — judgment call" |
| Rule existed? | "No" |
| Proposed fix | "Write ADR-NNNN + update PATTERNS.md §4" |
| Fix layer | "Layer 1 (Patterns)" |

## The four valid fix layers

Preference order: higher numbers descending into lower.

| Layer | When | Action |
|---|---|---|
| **3 Automated** | Mechanically detectable | Add lint, schema, or boundary rule |
| **1 Patterns** | Judgment call with defensible answer | Write ADR + update PATTERNS.md |
| **2 Process** | Coordination issue, not code | Update DoD / ROLE_SPECS / TEAM_PROTOCOL |
| **4 Launch** | Launch-prompt ambiguity | Update TEAM_LAUNCH_TEMPLATE |

## Output

Append to `docs/FRAMEWORK_CHANGELOG.md`:

```markdown
## YYYY-MM-DD — <feature> retrospective

### Issues observed
- **<issue>**: <description>
  - Auto-catchable? <yes/no>
  - Existing rule? <yes/no>
  - Fix: <layer> — <action>

### Near-misses / gaps
- ...

### What worked
- ...

### Lead's decisions
- [x] Approved & landed: <fix>
- [ ] Deferred: <fix> — reason: <...>
```

## Anti-patterns

- "Everything went great" → false; find at least one improvement
- Proposing Layer 1 when Layer 3 would work
- Rejecting without recording reason
- Lead implementing fixes silently (every change appears in changelog)
